es his loyalty he displays that loyalty rather fiercely.  He might be rude, brash, insulting and sometimes just a little bit selfish, but I'd never question his loyalty.<br>
<br>
Arma's been with TWC longer than the lifespan of some guilds.  His skills rock.  If you were ever fortunate enough to group with him, you'd recognize this.<br>
<br>
In Kael, we arrived, Fam pulled, we buffed because it looked like they didn't have forces, GoL arrived, they killed AoW, we moved on.  I don't remember a single /ooc, /shout, or any comment from anyone from our guild.  I do recall seeing a few goading comments from those who killed AoW, and some from spectators either supporting them, or otherwise.  We moved on.  Remember, this thread was started by Mezzum, who is not in TWC.<br>
<br>
As for VT we'd CoH'ed up to prep for TXD and the blobs, finished them, got loot and moved on.  I don't know that anyone expected ToS to fail, we've done AHR with about that many on evenings when the spawn was late.  Somewhere around 40 is adequate for AHR.  Somewhere around 70 appears to be right for the move through VT to clear it all.  YMMV.  Why all of a sudden 70 for clearing VT is a &quot;zerg force&quot; is beyond me.  70 for AHR herself is an Overwhelming Force.<br>
<br>
There is a difference between &quot;Overwhelming Force&quot; and &quot;Zerg Force&quot;.  An overwhelming force goes into an encounter and ends up with 1 or 2 deaths.  A Zerg Force has bodies strewn all over the floor and wouldn't have made it except by sheer numbers.  Zerg forces use &quot;cannon fodder&quot; to wear down an enemy.  I've seen us do some &quot;Zerg Force&quot; wins.  I've also seen us do &quot;Overwhelming Force&quot;.<br>
<br>
As for our &quot;wipe&quot; to AHR last week, it wasn't a total wipe.  It was kind of a fun evening in that &quot;we didn't get any cool loot, but we did things we'd never tried before&quot; sort of way.  We had all the forces in our usual pull positions.  AHR was brought in and *BAM* 32Ks all around.  I wish  I had screenshotted it.  It was the perfect example for &quot;Area of Effect&quot; as the dead/live charcter line transcribed a perfect circle.  We rezzed up and went to bed.  Clerics out of the ae were untouched.  Someone said, &quot;You know - we could win that.&quot;<br>
<br>
Maybe ToS likes to do the mostest with the leastest.  Maybe we like to do &quot;lots&quot;.  Perhaps ToS's strats get in our way.  So far, it really doesn't matter (other than warder coding problems).  We still make stuff dead - &quot;lots&quot;.<br>
<br>
- brkat<br>
<br>
